{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"obnoxious-ogreish-neontetra","creation_channel":"cli","description":"The Reconciler Heartbeat / Binding-Drift canary (.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge-canary.yml) auto-closes its bot-authored ALERT bug ticket on recovery via 'rebar transition <id> open closed --reason ... --force-close=...' at lines ~296 (heartbeat) and ~405 (binding-drift). Both OMIT --class. Since ticket ed13 made --class REQUIRED for bug close (even with --force-close), both steps fail: 'Error: closing a bug ticket requires --class'. Latent until a recovery fires the close path; EXPOSED post-f436 (bridge-fsck binding drift recovered to zero, firing the line-405 close) -> Reconciler Heartbeat Canary red on origin/main (runs 29704052374, 29705865824). Fix: add --class (env_integration) to both close commands. Discovered while verifying GitHub Actions on main after the rebar-debug batch.","id":"0e15-5252-fc34-4b89","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"reconcile-bridge-canary close-on-recovery steps omit --class, break bug-close under ed13 (red main)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784504271208172001,"uuid":"19bc0edb-e2e0-4838-8f7a-bbe894a4c476"}